# 🔹 Task 1: Explore Docker (Basic + Important Commands)

## 🧱 Step 1: Install Docker (Ubuntu)

Run:

```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt install docker.io -y
```

Start and enable Docker:

```bash
sudo systemctl start docker
sudo systemctl enable docker
```

Check version:

```bash
docker --version
```

Add permission (so no sudo needed):

```bash
sudo usermod -aG docker $USER
newgrp docker
```

---

## 🚀 Step 2: Core Docker Commands

### 📦 Image Commands

```bash
docker pull node          # Download image
docker images             # List images
docker rmi <image_id>     # Delete image
```

---

### 📦 Container Commands

```bash
docker run -it ubuntu bash     # Run container
docker ps                      # Running containers
docker ps -a                   # All containers
docker stop <id>               # Stop container
docker start <id>              # Start container
docker rm <id>                 # Delete container
```

---

### 🔍 Inspect & Logs

```bash
docker logs <container_id>
docker exec -it <container_id> bash
```

---

💡 *Think like this:*

* Image = template
* Container = running app

